fish- true pericula clownfish, yellow tang, coral beauty, algae blenny, and a scooter blenny

title: For Sale/Trade:  Spyderco SpyderFly Butterfly Bali Flipper VG-10 Knife
postcontent:
The spyder ate the fly. The SpyderFly infuses traditional Balisong (or Butterfly) knife elements with innovative Spyderco features. Balis are all about swinging, sometimes called doing the dance. Eric Glesser, the designer of the SpyderFly, incorporates Spydercos Trademark Round Hole into both handles. The holes position the thumb and fingers (pinching either side of the handle) for superb control while indexing/rotating and enhancing fluidity of the swing. Contours and valleys lining the handle offer friction resistance keeping The Fly firmly in grip while maneuvering. A spring-loaded locking lever attaches to either handle for left- or right-hand use and locks the blade closed (but not open) for safe carry inside a pocket. Squeezing the handles together releases the locks lever. The blade is VG-10, that is hollow-ground and sharpened on one side only. Straight down the center of the blade, a dagger grind balances out both sides of the knife, again designed for smoother and even swinging. Manipulating the wire pocket clip to either handle or either side of the knife sets it up for a variety of carry options and draw positions. The SpyderFly links all that is utilitarian in a traditional Balisong with innovative features youve come to expect from Spyderco.

Specifications:
Overall Length: 9.75"
Blade Length: 4.125"
Blade Material: VG-10
Closed Length: 6"
Handle Length: 5.6"
Weight: 6 oz.

postcontent:
I have an 1884 rifle to saddle carbine conversion.  The conversion was done a very long time ago and possibly an armory conversion.  Its a 1884 model made in 1893, per the LWP proof.  Most of the stock proofs are still visible (LWP 1893, Circle P).  Their are added (#14, and 292) stamped into the stock.  These are more than likely rack numbers.  The stock has been refinished prior to me owning it.   The carbine has the standard US Springfield with  the eagle proof.  The barrel band has the correct "U" stamped on it.  The butt plate has the "US" proof, and has the trapdoor for the cleaning rod.  The sights are the correct time period buffington rear sight.  It has a original saddle bar but has a reproduction ring.  The barrel shows wear, but rifling is still good for a 119 year old gun.  Their are dings scrapes and stuff.  I have almost 2 full boxes of Black Powder ammo that comes with the rifle.  

I would like $650 or best reasonable offer for it.  But I would trade it for a older Gibson 5 string or 4 (tenor) banjo with a resonator back.  The rifle is worth more in parts but I don't want to part it out.   Reproductions cost $1500 but you get a original 1884 for $650.  I may consider other trades aswell, let me know what you have.

title: Want To Buy:  lease ranch land for target shooting, non-commercial, 20-30 minutes form Parker area
postcontent:
I am an avid target shooter and am looking for a ranch or other vacant property within 20-30 min drive of Parker, CO to lease legal space for target shooting. Not interested in hunting on your land, but interested in being able to set up targets, have distances measured, be able to leave a sun cover tent up, in the summer, and targets up, (obviously in good condition. I will not be using this for commercial purposes, but it is very difficult to find a range that allows true long gun shooting, and, when I shoot, I like to do it safely, which generally means being away form other people. Clean up brass and garbage each time out, and willing to discuss other requirements/suggestions. It would be nice to come home form work and grab a go bag and let off some steam. It would also be nice to have a table set up so as to be able to sight in a rifle properly, and without pressure and range concerns.

I am a licensed attorney, and would provide you with a release as to any injuries caused by me, as well as indemnifying you for any damage, although I am ethically advised to tell you to have another attorney review it. I am a handshake guy, and, as long as we communicate with activity on the area, chances of injury are minimal. form time to time I woudl probably like to bring out one or two people, but, again, not for commercial purposes. If you are a shooter/hunter, and have been looking for someone to shoot with, or put together a small range I am thinking it will not be that wide, but woudl like 500 yards max, this could be a nice project. although I am an avid Sporting clay person, due to the clays, I was not planning on asking to shoot clays out there. However, it would be nice to leave up a Caldwell Gong other reactionary targets, and be able to get out there and start shooting, instead of having to set up and take down each time.

If you are interested, please contact me. We can discuss details further. Obviously, we can write up a lot of documents and rules, and should, but this is a handshake understanding, in the sense, that no matter what you may charge for the privilege of shooting on your land, it is your land and it is a privilege to shoot on it.

Please contact me at REDACTED, or REDACTED.

Brett D. Chardavoyne
